---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const publishDate = new Date('2024-01-15');
const author = "Astro Developer";
const readingTime = "3 min read";
---

<Layout title="My First Blog Post" description="Getting started with Astro blogging">
    <Header />
    <main>
        <article class="blog-post">
            <header class="post-header">
                <h1>Getting Started with Astro</h1>
                <div class="post-meta">
                    <span>By {author}</span>
                    <span>•</span>
                    <time datetime={publishDate.toISOString()}>
                        {publishDate.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { 
                            year: 'numeric', 
                            month: 'long', 
                            day: 'numeric' 
                        })}
                    </time>
                    <span>•</span>
                    <span>{readingTime}</span>
                </div>
            </header>
            
            <div class="post-content">
                <p>
                    Welcome to my first blog post built with Astro! This post demonstrates 
                    how easy it is to create content-rich pages using Astro's file-based 
                    routing system.
                </p>
                
                <h2>Why Choose Astro?</h2>
                <p>
                    Astro offers several compelling advantages for modern web development:
                </p>
                
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Performance First:</strong> Ships zero JavaScript by default</li>
                    <li><strong>Framework Agnostic:</strong> Use React, Vue, Svelte, or vanilla JS</li>
                    <li><strong>Islands Architecture:</strong> Interactive components only where needed</li>
                    <li><strong>Developer Experience:</strong> Built-in TypeScript and great tooling</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h2>File-based Routing</h2>
                <p>
                    This blog post exists at <code>/blog/first-post</code> because the file 
                    is located at <code>src/pages/blog/first-post.astro</code>. Astro 
                    automatically creates routes based on your file structure.
                </p>
                
                <blockquote>
                    <p>
                        "Astro lets you use your favorite UI framework to build 
                        static sites that load lightning fast with zero client-side JavaScript."
                    </p>
                </blockquote>
                
                <h2>What's Next?</h2>
                <p>
                    In future posts, we'll explore more advanced Astro features like:
                </p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Content collections for better content management</li>
                    <li>API routes for dynamic functionality</li>
                    <li>Integrations with popular services</li>
                    <li>Deployment strategies</li>
                </ol>
                
                <p>
                    Thanks for reading! Feel free to explore the rest of this demo site 
                    to see more Astro features in action.
                </p>
            </div>
        </article>
    </main>
    <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
    main {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 2rem;
        min-height: calc(100vh - 200px);
    }
    
    .blog-post {
        line-height: 1.7;
    }
    
    .post-header {
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
        text-align: center;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #e1e8ed;
        padding-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    
    .post-header h1 {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        color: #2c3e50;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    
    .post-meta {
        color: #6c757d;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.5rem;
    }
    
    .post-content h2 {
        color: #34495e;
        margin-top: 2.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        font-size: 1.5rem;
    }
    
    .post-content p {
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    
    .post-content ul, .post-content ol {
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        padding-left: 2rem;
    }
    
    .post-content li {
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    
    code {
        background: #f1f3f5;
        padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem;
        border-radius: 3px;
        font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
        font-size: 0.9em;
    }
    
    blockquote {
        margin: 2rem 0;
        padding: 1rem 2rem;
        background: #f8f9fa;
        border-left: 4px solid #3498db;
        font-style: italic;
    }
    
    blockquote p {
        margin: 0;
    }
    
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        main {
            padding: 1rem;
        }
        
        .post-header h1 {
            font-size: 2rem;
        }
        
        .post-meta {
            flex-direction: column;
            gap: 0.25rem;
        }
    }
</style>